 were predicted by the minimum description length (MDL) of the hypothesized LOT","targetRectangle":{"y":565.39321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":657.44000000000005,"height":64.5}},{"text":"This fuses two aspects of geometric shape representations that are partly independent, format (LOT) and selection (MDL), and uses MDL data to argue for LOT—highly indirect evidence","targetRectangle":{"y":629.89321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":658.04999999999995,"height":90.5}},{"text":"Current study provides more direct evidence for tree structure in geometric shape representations in 3 online experiments with adults","targetRectangle":{"y":720.39321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":611.35999999999979,"height":52}},{"text":"50 subjects | 128 trials","targetRectangle":{"y":1205.4366458058357,"x":25.25,"width":138.09600000000003,"height":18}},{"text":"Modified congruent","targetRectangle":{"y":1020.0550538599491,"x":472.52647352218628,"width":86.970000000000027,"height":13}},{"text":"Matches","targetRectangle":{"y":1003.567322075367,"x":352.91987013816833,"width":53.269999999999982,"height":18}},{"text":"+","targetRectangle":{"y":1042.428833335638,"x":201.32562255859375,"width":7.4199999999999875,"height":17}},{"text":"Depth 2","targetRectangle":{"y":1792.2629391849041,"x":268.38426148891449,"width":24.779999999999973,"height":9}},{"text":"***","targetRectangle":{"y":1772.9473879933357,"x":751.7754799425602,"width":16.758000000000038,"height":18}},{"text":"Samples","targetRectangle":{"y":1328.3403316736221,"x":135.52167236804962,"width":76.949999999999989,"height":26}},{"text":"Same subtree","targetRectangle":{"y":1374.2624513208866,"x":364.82446956634521,"width":61.389999999999986,"height":13}},{"text":"**","targetRectangle":{"y":913.85382080078125,"x":965.64881134033203,"width":10.896484375,"height":17}},{"text":" ","targetRectangle":{"y":1706.4832765161991,"x":905.66656486690044,"width":2.6000000000000227,"height":13}},{"text":"50 subjects | 256 trials