8,"width":53.269999999999982,"height":18}},{"text":"Background","targetRectangle":{"y":429.89321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":165.12,"height":45}},{"text":"We build on the recent proposal that geometric shapes are represented in a language of thought (LOT) consisting of a handful of primitives that can be combined to recreate the encoded shape (Sablé-Meyer et al. 2022)","targetRectangle":{"y":474.89321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":654.16999999999996,"height":90.5}},{"text":"Adults’ reaction times and error rates in encoding shapes were predicted by the minimum description length (MDL) of the hypothesized LOT","targetRectangle":{"y":565.39321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":657.44000000000005,"height":64.5}},{"text":"This fuses two aspects of geometric shape representations that are partly independent, format (LOT) and selection (MDL), and uses MDL data to argue for LOT—highly indirect evidence","targetRectangle":{"y":629.89321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":658.04999999999995,"height":90.5}},{"text":"Current study provides more direct evidence for tree structure in geometric shape representations in 3 online experiments with adults","targetRectangle":{"y":720.39321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":611.35999999999979,"height":52}},{"text":"50 subjects | 128 trials","targetRectangle":{"y":1205.4366458058357,"x":25.25,"width":138.09600000000003,"height":18}},{"text":"Modified congruent","targetRectangle":{"y":1020.0550538599491,"x":472.52647352218628,"width":86.970000000000027,"height":13}},{"text":"Matches","targetRectangle":{"y":1003.567322075367,"x":352.91987013816833,"width":53.269999999999982,"height":18}},{"text":"+","targetRectangle":{"y":1042.428833335638,"x":201.32562255859375,"width":7.4199999999999875,"height":17}},{"text":"Depth 2","targetRectangle":{"y":1792.2629391849041,"x":268.38426148891449,"width":24.779999999999973,"height":9}},{"text":"***","targetRectangle":{"y":1772.9473879933357,"x":751.7754799425602,