}},{"text":"repeat","targetRectangle":{"y":741.66555750370026,"x":900.92628685951229,"width":29.889999999999986,"height":13}},{"text":"3 times","targetRectangle":{"y":754.66555750370026,"x":899.63128685951233,"width":32.480000000000018,"height":13}},{"text":"Experiment 2: Subtree Facilitation","targetRectangle":{"y":1165.9140625,"x":25.25,"width":469.17000000000007,"height":39}},{"text":"Experiment 3: Movement Depth","targetRectangle":{"y":1545.1591796875,"x":25.25,"width":434.40000000000009,"height":39}},{"text":"Structure","targetRectangle":{"y":1357.4323733448982,"x":144.43370878696442,"width":58.744,"height":18}},{"text":"1","targetRectangle":{"y":911.84134981036186,"x":225.84444379806519,"width":5.5999999999999943,"height":13}},{"text":"Matches","targetRectangle":{"y":1724.1312258839607,"x":389.04505324363708,"width":53.269999999999982,"height":18}},{"text":"Background","targetRectangle":{"y":429.89321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":165.12,"height":45}},{"text":"We build on the recent proposal that geometric shapes are represented in a language of thought (LOT) consisting of a handful of primitives that can be combined to recreate the encoded shape (Sablé-Meyer et al. 2022)","targetRectangle":{"y":474.89321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":654.16999999999996,"height":90.5}},{"text":"Adults’ reaction times and error rates in encoding shapes were predicted by the minimum description length (MDL) of the hypothesized LOT","targetRectangle":{"y":565.39321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":657.44000000000005,"height":64.5}},{"text":"This fuses two aspects of geometric shape representations that are partly independent, format (LOT) and selection (MDL), and uses MDL data to argue for LOT—highly indirect evidence","targetRectangle":{"y":629.89321899414062,"x":28.606538772583008,"width":658.04999999999995,"height":90.5}},{"text":"Current study provides more direct evidence for tree structure in geometric shape representations in 3 online experiments